  <title class="- topic/title ">Prepare to Use Category Affinity</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">To use category affinity, you must
	 first turn on the Category Activity Recorder. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <steps id="steps_C8861BDC3E874B7996C8911329FA5D55" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_978F658BA4D54130A6E0AC97050BD041" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the Locations Home Page, click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Profiles</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_2A1654F5B0A648E49F272E069C5E02D6" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Press<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Start</uicontrol> on the 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">user.category
				Affinity</uicontrol> row. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tip:</b> Start
				recording right away. Because category affinity is based on users' returning
				visits, the more data recorded, the more accurate category affinity will be. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
